# Mission Planning: Accessing Charts and Preparing Your JSA

Before you submit a CASA application or fly any mission, you need to know how to find the right aviation documents and prepare a proper Job Safety Assessment. These are the practical tasks that trip up new ReOC holders — not because they're difficult, but because nobody walks you through where things actually are.

This guide covers accessing aviation charts and aerodrome data, and preparing a JSA that will hold up under audit.

Author: Rachel Ng

Last review: 3 May 2026

